<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I've noticed that in various places throughout the framework, objects make getDefaultControllerName(), getDefaultAction(), and getDefaultModule() method calls on objects of type Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Interface.  Those methods are not defined in Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Interface, which can obviously lead to problems.  These methods are defined in Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Abstract, so it probably slipped by.  However, if one were to create the class My_Controller_Dispatcher_Abstract from which all application dispatchers inherit, there would be major problems if the methods mentioned above were not defined.</p>

<p>I haven't scoured the entire framework, but know that the above methods are called in Zend_Controller_Front and Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module from object properties that are defined as type Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Interface.</p>

